{"questionId":"9066638","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Technetium-99m, a widely used radionuclide, has a half-life of 6.0 hours and undergoes gamma decay to technetium-99.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Most of the nuclear waste generated in a hospital is low-level waste (LLW).</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Outline the disposal of LLW.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">stored in shielded containers until radiation level drops «to a safe level»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066638","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ1.b(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Outline the disposal of LLW.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.8 Nuclear medicine (HL only)","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}